1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an adjacency labeling scheme for graphs, which is a topic closely related to data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The family of power-law graphs is commonly used to model various types of networks, including social and information networks. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions the Internet AS-level graph as an example of a power-law graph, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed labeling scheme, which is related to system optimization and control. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - Graph theory is a fundamental topic in game theory, and the paper deals with labeling schemes for graphs, which could be relevant to game theory applications.
